Step Ordering <p>Data generation is done exactly once, in the first step of the pipeline.</p> <p>Using the <code>simulation_step</code> function, we generate an <code>MCStep</code> object that samples the DGP model with a given simulation specification.</p> <pre><code>datagen_step = simulation_step(
    T=T,
    shocks={
        "g,z": Shock(T=T, dist="norm", multivar=True, seed=0),
        "r": Shock(T=T, dist="norm", seed=1),
    },
    observables=True,
)
</code></pre> <p><code>simulation_step</code> takes all <code>kwarg</code>s that <code>SolvedModel.sim</code> accepts. Each MC iteration will trigger a simulation with this specification and passthrough the output data.</p>
